column2: Denotes whether a species is a migrant or resident; values are either "migrant" or "resident"
Sex, if the study specified differences in survival and/or probability of captures for males and females; if no specification, "species-level" denotes that estimates were made for a species only.
phi indicates the apparent survival estimate, taken from the literature.
standard error associated with phi survival estimates, taken from the literature; if no value, then "NA"
Lower Confidence Interval (LCI) of the survival estimate; if no value, then "NA"
Upper Confidence Interval (UCI) of the survival estimate; if no value, then "NA"
Probability of capture estimate, taken from the literature; if no value, then "NA"
standard error associated with p estimates, taken from the literature; if no value, then "NA"
Sample size of individuals studied for estimates of apparent survival and capture probability.
Rate of recapture, as reported in the literature, calculated as # individuals recaptured/total number of individuals captured initially.
Literature reference corresponding to each estimate. See Literature Cited in Williamson & Witt manuscript for full details.
